{
  "url": "https://www.hymnal.net/en/hymn/ns/761",
  "title": "In these times of restlessness",
  "verses": [
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In these times of restlessness,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In these times of uncertainty,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When all we trusted has become"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But sand and we sink helplessly,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Reaching out, a Rock we hold."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He is still and unshakable."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eternally and silently,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He waited for us with love untold."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "How we think we have control"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When all things go predictably,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But when waves crash, when storm winds blast,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We see our human frailty."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Then He’s always there to say,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“It is I, do not be afraid.”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "It’s up to us to take Him in"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Our boats, our lives, for Him e’er to stay."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So that’s why we call, “O Lord Jesus!”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Desper’tely for peace inside"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And peace He gives,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A peace beyond understanding."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And still then we call, “O Lord Jesus!”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Just to find the peace supplied"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Is Christ Himself resting in our being."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    }
  ],
